1
Collaborate with founders to define and implement the company’s strategic roadmap,
focusing on growth in sales, marketing, and operations.
Oversee workflows and processes to enhance scalability, efficiency, and cross-
functional communication.
Drive sales and marketing initiatives, developing data-driven strategies for lead
generation, customer engagement, and brand visibility.
Provide strategic insights, manage key projects, and coordinate high-profile initiatives
with an emphasis on business growth.
Advise founders on strategic and operational matters, support team skill
development, and foster a culture of innovation and collaboration.
Qualifications

● Experience: Minimum 2- 4 years in a founder’s office, business analyst, project
management, or analytics role in a high-growth environment, preferably within SaaS
or consumer start-up.
● Business Acumen: Strong understanding of business strategy with the ability to
synthesize complex goals into actionable plans.
● Analytical Skills: Skilled in data analysis and presentation, with the ability to draw
insights from data and make data-driven recommendations.
● Communication: Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to foster strong
relationships and collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams.
● Organizational Skills: Proven ability to prioritize and manage multiple initiatives
simultaneously with a high level of organization.
● Industry Knowledge: Experience in healthcare or technology is preferred but not
required.
● Education: Bachelor’s degree in Business, Operations, or related field; an advanced
degree is a plus.
Benefits

● Competitive Salary & Bonus: We offer a competitive salary and performance-
based bonuses.
● Health & Wellness: Comprehensive healthcare and wellness benefits.
● Professional Growth: Access to learning and development opportunities.
● Collaborative Culture: Be part of a dynamic, innovative environment where your input helps shape the company’s future.
